Preheat your oven to 200°C and bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}. Halve the @plums{2}, remove the stone and chop each half into 4 pieces. Peel and finely chop the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and finely chopped) (or use a #garlic press{}). Chop the @potatoes{450}(peeled and cut into 2cm chunks). Trim the @spring onion{1} and thinly slice. Season the @skin-on British chicken breasts{2} with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook until you can easily slip a #knife{} through, ~{15-20%minutes}. Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, lay the chicken breasts in the pan skin side down, fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}. Turn them over and cook for ~{1-2%minutes} on the flesh side. Transfer them to a #baking tray{}, skin side up. Pop into your oven and roast until golden brown and cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Add a little more @oil to the frying pan (no need to wash) and pop back on medium high heat. Once hot, add the @shredded Savoy cabbage{150} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir fry until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute} more. Add a splash of @water, stir and reduce the heat to medium. Cover the pan with a #lid{} and cook until the cabbage is tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Pop into a #bowl{} and cover with #tin foil{} to keep warm.

Pop your pan back on medium high heat and add a knob of @?butter{1%knob} (if you have it). Let it gently melt. If you don't have any butter use a drizzle of @?oil{} instead. Add the plums to the pan and fry, stirring frequently, until they begin to colour, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the @honey{15%ml} to the pan, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}, then stir in the @water{100%ml} and the @chicken stock powder{1}. Bring to the boil, reduce the heat and simmer until the sauce is sticky and the plums softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the chicken is cooked, remove from the oven, and allow to rest for a couple of ~{minutes} on a #cutting board{}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan off the heat. Add a knob of @?butter{1%knob} and a splash of @?milk{1%splash} (if you have any) and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir in the spring onion. Cover with a lid to keep warm.

Taste the plum sauce and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if you feel it needs it, add a splash of @?water{} if it's a bit thick. Thinly slice the chicken. Serve the garlicky cabbage and potatoes on plates with the plum sauce alongside, topped with the chicken. Enjoy!